Open, clean, airy, and the spectacular view of the monona bay toward the Capitol.
It's a perfect place to pick up a cup of coffee and sit at one of the cozy table and read paper/check email or quietly chat with a friend.
I love the large window that makes the room bright.
A telescope next to the window completes the scene.
Coffee is pretty good.
I don't think I can recommend the espresso drinks.
But just come for a cup of joe and have a serene morning.
There's an outdoor seating for summer season, too.

I discovered this gem with my mom one day when we were exploring the list of slow food week participants.
