The problems started with my order.
I ordered the quiche of the day and sat down.
15 min pass and they came to my table and said they were out of what I ordered.
I switched to what's left, no problem.
Another 15 min passed and I went to the front and they told me it was a very busy day and that it was almost ready.
(It was less busy than an average lunch rush at most places I have been in town.
) When I finally got the quiche it was cold and blah.
I hope to try again and experience what everyone is talking about.
It stands on 3 stars for being a cool hang out.

